- Oh, yes. Miss!

727
01:00:14,400 --> 01:00:18,359
- That girl wanted to talk to you.
- Thank you.

728
01:00:21,040 --> 01:00:23,076
Hi.

729
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:25,669
You're not who I was looking for.

730
01:00:25,920 --> 01:00:28,275
- Are you Noreen?
- Listen, mister...

731
01:00:28,560 --> 01:00:31,950
You were looking for Spenser
at La Fonda hotel.

732
01:00:32,160 --> 01:00:33,957
- No! Wait!
- Hey, watch it.

733
01:00:36,720 --> 01:00:40,713
Noreen, I just want to talk to you!
Listen to me!

734
01:00:40,920 --> 01:00:43,275
- I can help you.
- You're not FBI?

735
01:00:43,480 --> 01:00:44,310
No!

736
01:00:44,680 --> 01:00:46,398
- You're not FBI?
- No!

737
01:00:46,680 --> 01:00:50,116
Okay, but we gotta
go someplace safe.

738
01:00:50,320 --> 01:00:52,675
I have a white Volkswagen.

739
01:00:52,880 --> 01:00:54,279
- They followed me.
- Who?

740
01:00:54,520 --> 01:00:56,317
The feds. They want their money.

741
01:00:56,640 --> 01:00:58,073
They know where the money is.

742
01:00:58,280 --> 01:01:01,317
They said if I found Bob for them,
they would let me off.

743
01:01:01,560 --> 01:01:04,120
I came here because Bob
loves the rodeo.

744
01:01:04,360 --> 01:01:06,874
- Bobby's dead.
- Oh, Jesus.

745
01:01:07,080 --> 01:01:09,548
You sure they were feds? FBI?

746
01:01:09,760 --> 01:01:13,878
I told him it wouldn't work,
to just give the money back.

747
01:01:14,080 --> 01:01:16,310
What wasn't gonna work?

748
01:01:16,560 --> 01:01:19,074
Ten days ago,
his friend shows up...

749
01:01:19,280 --> 01:01:22,397
...says he has a plan to get
the FBI off us.

750
01:01:22,640 --> 01:01:26,713
That way we could stay together
and still keep the money.

751
01:01:26,960 --> 01:01:28,473
What was his name?

752
01:01:28,720 --> 01:01:32,998
It wasn't Bobby's idea
to take the money from the bureau.

753
01:01:33,240 --> 01:01:35,071
He just wanted to stay with me.

754
01:01:35,320 --> 01:01:39,154
- What was the friend's name?
- I don't know!

755
01:01:41,520 --> 01:01:44,159
I have a picture of the three of us.

756
01:01:48,360 --> 01:01:52,035
Maybe it's in my car.

757
01:01:57,720 --> 01:01:58,994
Ray. Hey, Ray!

758
01:02:01,680 --> 01:02:03,238
FBI. Internal Affairs.

759
01:02:18,520 --> 01:02:21,671
We just want to
ask you some questions.

760
01:02:21,880 --> 01:02:23,279
Let's take a ride.

761
01:02:41,360 --> 01:02:43,351
Hey! What the hell?

762
01:02:44,480 --> 01:02:46,436
- Give me the keys.
- They're in it.

763
01:02:46,680 --> 01:02:49,558
What happened? Where's Bob?

764
01:02:49,960 --> 01:02:54,078
Wait a minute!
Gorman, my horse is tied to the back!

765
01:03:02,640 --> 01:03:06,474
We've been looking all over
New Mexico for you.

766
01:03:06,720 --> 01:03:09,917
We didn't expect you
to call yourself Spenser.

767
01:03:10,160 --> 01:03:13,470
Maybe you were in on it
and helped Artie.

768
01:03:13,920 --> 01:03:17,276
Four months ago,
a lot of money disappeared...

769
01:03:17,480 --> 01:03:19,277
...from bureau impound.

770
01:03:19,480 --> 01:03:21,596
- Sound familiar?
- No.

771
01:03:21,800 --> 01:03:23,518
You don't have to answer.

772
01:03:23,960 --> 01:03:26,315
Yeah, questions.
A lot of unanswered questions.

773
01:03:26,480 --> 01:03:27,708
Right.

774
01:03:27,920 --> 01:03:29,672
We're taking you to the police.

775
01:03:29,880 --> 01:03:33,793
You won't need a lawyer unless
you're hiding something.

776
01:03:34,040 --> 01:03:35,871
What's he doing?

777
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:37,915
[HONKS CAR HORN]

778
01:03:50,640 --> 01:03:52,073
Wave him by.

779
01:04:00,160 --> 01:04:01,832
What's he doing?

780
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:04,555
Hey, watch out!

781
01:04:24,680 --> 01:04:25,908
You guys drunk?

782
01:04:37,280 --> 01:04:40,238
My God, what happened to you?

783
01:04:40,680 --> 01:04:42,591
- Where's Gorman?
- I don't know.

784
01:04:42,840 --> 01:04:46,913
He took off with the truck.
He didn't say anything.

785
01:04:47,160 --> 01:04:50,277
I just want to know
what's going on.

786
01:04:50,520 --> 01:04:53,080
You don't even know who I am.

787
01:04:56,040 --> 01:04:59,077
My name is Ray Dolezal. I'm a cop.

788
01:04:59,480 --> 01:05:02,552
I'm trying to figure out
who killed Spenser.

789
01:05:06,920 --> 01:05:08,558
I'm sorry.

790
01:05:34,160 --> 01:05:35,957
Get the car.

791
01:05:36,160 --> 01:05:38,549
Get the car!

792
01:06:28,360 --> 01:06:29,270
He's back.

793
01:07:22,360 --> 01:07:23,395
Ray?

794
01:07:23,960 --> 01:07:25,473
You all right?

795
01:07:34,080 --> 01:07:35,752
Who killed that girl tonight?

796
01:07:36,280 --> 01:07:40,671
<i>- We should tell somebody.</i>
RAY: <i>I can keep you out of this.</i>

797
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:43,314
LANE:
<i>I don 't want to be kept out of this.</i>

798
01:07:43,560 --> 01:07:47,599
<i>I care about you.</i>
<i>I don 't care about Lennox or the FBI.</i>

799
01:07:47,920 --> 01:07:49,672
I care about you.

800
01:07:51,240 --> 01:07:53,470
I want you.

801
01:08:04,080 --> 01:08:06,150
I'm married, Lane.

802
01:08:07,560 --> 01:08:09,755
You want to go back to your wife?

803
01:08:14,560 --> 01:08:16,516
Do you need money?

804
01:08:17,040 --> 01:08:18,678
I can get you money.

805
01:08:19,360 --> 01:08:22,477
You can pay off the feds,
make them disappear.

806
01:08:24,120 --> 01:08:25,758
I'll get you some money.

807
01:09:10,080 --> 01:09:11,559
[LANE MOANS]

808
01:09:12,880 --> 01:09:14,233
LANE:
<i>Oh, God!</i>

809
01:09:16,880 --> 01:09:19,838
Oh, yes. Oh, yes...

810
01:09:23,280 --> 01:09:24,759
Yes!

811
01:09:25,880 --> 01:09:26,949
Ow... yes!

812
01:09:27,480 --> 01:09:30,950
Yes... yes!

813
01:09:31,680 --> 01:09:32,999
Oh, God! Yes.

814
01:09:34,200 --> 01:09:36,919
Get down, Deputy Ray.
Get down.

815
01:09:37,560 --> 01:09:40,313
LANE:
<i>Oh, yes. Oh, thank you!</i>

816
01:09:42,080 --> 01:09:43,274
God...

817
01:10:05,320 --> 01:10:06,912
Don't do it!

818
01:10:09,960 --> 01:10:12,758
The guys at the rodeo
were FBI too, right?

819
01:10:13,000 --> 01:10:16,629
It's a big bureau,
lots of headless horsemen.

820
01:10:16,880 --> 01:10:19,917
- Can I put on pants?
- You killed them.

821
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:22,634
Go ahead, shoot me. Do it!

822
01:10:22,920 --> 01:10:25,115
You think it'll solve things?

823
01:10:25,320 --> 01:10:28,153
The murder of a federal agent?

824
01:10:31,720 --> 01:10:36,714
My first concern was the operation's
integrity. It was a judgment call.

825
01:10:36,920 --> 01:10:38,956
- Go outside.
- I'm fine.

826
01:10:39,160 --> 01:10:40,559
Wait in the car.

827
01:10:41,240 --> 01:10:43,754
The less you know, the better.

828
01:10:46,400 --> 01:10:50,632
- You drilling her, Ray?
- Did Artie know the money was stolen?

829
01:10:50,920 --> 01:10:55,038
Washington wouldn't fund my
sting so I borrowed it.

830
01:10:55,400 --> 01:10:59,109
Artie went ballistic when
Internal Affairs showed up.

831
01:10:59,320 --> 01:11:04,235
So you killed him, left the cash
and hoped he'd be blamed.

832
01:11:04,520 --> 01:11:09,150
- No, not me. I told Artie the truth.
- Your truth.

833
01:11:11,280 --> 01:11:13,157
I'm putting on my pants.

834
01:11:26,760 --> 01:11:27,954
Jesus!

835
01:11:34,600 --> 01:11:36,716
Ray, Ray, Ray.

836
01:11:39,920 --> 01:11:42,309
You'll appreciate this story.

837
01:11:43,520 --> 01:11:46,353
When I finally found Artie...

838
01:11:46,600 --> 01:11:49,956
...he's holed up
in the local Ranch Motel...

839
01:11:50,200 --> 01:11:53,875
...waiting for Lennox,
thanks to your friend Lane.

840
01:11:55,360 --> 01:11:59,672
His plan has come apart.
Reality is setting in.

841
01:12:03,120 --> 01:12:05,918
He thought I was gonna save him.

842
01:12:06,200 --> 01:12:10,990
I drive us out to nowhere and
then I tell him the truth.

843
01:12:11,520 --> 01:12:13,192
His wife knows...

844
01:12:13,400 --> 01:12:16,756
...he's fucking Noreen
and he's fucking Lane!

845
01:12:17,040 --> 01:12:18,917
- Bullshit.
- Ask her!

846
01:12:19,200 --> 01:12:23,113
Bring Lane in here and ask
if he wasn't in before you!

847
01:12:28,160 --> 01:12:31,277
I tell him that his life is shit...

848
01:12:31,480 --> 01:12:33,630
...and we're both fucked...

849
01:12:33,840 --> 01:12:36,274
...and there's no way out.

850
01:12:36,480 --> 01:12:37,754
And then...

851
01:12:38,880 --> 01:12:43,556
...I handed him the gun
and said, "You go first, buddy."

852
01:12:43,760 --> 01:12:45,512
And he shot himself.

853
01:12:47,440 --> 01:12:51,831
- I walked to town.
- I'm arresting you for his murder.

854
01:12:52,080 --> 01:12:56,915
And they'll believe you.
What picture will they be seeing?

855
01:12:57,160 --> 01:13:01,915
Small-town redneck who possibly
stole money from the FBI...

856
01:13:02,120 --> 01:13:06,955
...telling tales about a respected
senior minority agent...

857
01:13:07,200 --> 01:13:11,398
...who hasn't so much as a
bug stain on his record.

858
01:13:12,200 --> 01:13:13,758
I'm out of the loop.

859
01:13:14,200 --> 01:13:18,830
Artie's dead. Noreen's fingered
you as the accomplice.

860
01:13:19,080 --> 01:13:20,149
She's dead.

861
01:13:20,440 --> 01:13:24,228
All you've got is a Polaroid, cowboy!

862
01:13:24,480 --> 01:13:25,754
Means nothing!

863
01:13:27,040 --> 01:13:29,793
It's just another snapshot.

864
01:13:31,200 --> 01:13:34,397
If I help you bust Lennox,
what happens?

865
01:13:34,600 --> 01:13:37,831
Then you're a hero.
You get to go home.

866
01:13:38,040 --> 01:13:43,239
I say Artie stole the money. You and me
took a lemon and made lemonade.

867
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:47,311
It's your only move.

868
01:13:51,120 --> 01:13:53,315
You get back to me now, Ray.

869
01:13:53,920 --> 01:13:56,673
I'll be here. Waiting.

870
01:14:01,960 --> 01:14:03,439
[GREG GIGGLES]

871
01:14:14,800 --> 01:14:16,313
Lane?

872
01:14:38,480 --> 01:14:40,152
What are you doing here?

873
01:14:40,400 --> 01:14:43,392
- Have you seen Lane?
- No. You all right?

874
01:14:44,800 --> 01:14:47,109
I want to show you something.

875
01:14:59,960 --> 01:15:03,953
They made this a working holiday.
Do you believe that?

876
01:15:04,200 --> 01:15:06,919
Our tax dollars, hard at work.

877
01:15:09,720 --> 01:15:12,314
Good always triumphs over evil.

878
01:15:12,560 --> 01:15:16,314
Come on. Let's see
how much they know. Hop in.

879
01:15:37,600 --> 01:15:40,114
My number one rule in life...

880
01:15:40,960 --> 01:15:43,918
...is, don't let people intimidate you.

881
01:15:44,920 --> 01:15:47,559
Here you go. Payback.

882
01:15:49,880 --> 01:15:54,112
- You are a disappointment.
- I'm working for the FBI.

883
01:15:54,320 --> 01:15:57,915
No, you're not. I know who you are.

884
01:15:58,120 --> 01:15:59,519
I made calls.

885
01:15:59,760 --> 01:16:04,038
I know about Greg Meeker
and his pathetic little scam.

886
01:16:04,280 --> 01:16:07,113
I'm C-fucking-IA, Bobby.

887
01:16:09,120 --> 01:16:13,511
Meeker doesn't know shit.
He can't touch me.

888
01:16:13,720 --> 01:16:18,430
They don't tell him that, though.
Officially, I don't exist.

889
01:16:18,680 --> 01:16:20,113
I can't.

890
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:24,156
My profit's my reward...

891
01:16:24,400 --> 01:16:28,552
...for selfless service to
God and country.

892
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:30,919
No!

893
01:16:32,480 --> 01:16:35,916
What's the fuck's wrong?
I brought them here for you.

894
01:16:36,120 --> 01:16:41,035
They're the only ones
that can connect Artie to you.

895
01:16:41,280 --> 01:16:43,714
- Nobody'll ever know.
- I will.

896
01:16:45,120 --> 01:16:46,314
Yeah?

897
01:17:07,400 --> 01:17:11,313
Well, we're partners.
I'm action and you're money.

898
01:17:11,520 --> 01:17:13,158
We could be legendary.

899
01:17:13,800 --> 01:17:17,110
This isn't about sides.
This is about confusion.

900
01:17:17,400 --> 01:17:20,039
This is about creating enemies.

901
01:17:20,280 --> 01:17:22,953
The goddamn world's falling apart.

902
01:17:23,200 --> 01:17:26,112
Peace reigns. Freedom reigns.

903
01:17:26,360 --> 01:17:28,078
Democracy rules.

904
01:17:28,600 --> 01:17:32,036
How can we keep
the military/industrial complex...

905
01:17:32,400 --> 01:17:36,757
...chugging forward without
clear-cut, pit-faced...

906
01:17:37,000 --> 01:17:41,152
...scum-sucking evil
breathing down our neck?

907
01:17:43,080 --> 01:17:45,310
Threatening our very shores.

908
01:17:46,000 --> 01:17:48,753
Now, my job is to make sure...

909
01:17:49,000 --> 01:17:51,958
...the other side keeps on fighting.

910
01:17:52,200 --> 01:17:56,352
Whatever side
we're officially not on this year.

911
01:17:57,400 --> 01:17:59,595
But that's water under the bridge.

912
01:17:59,880 --> 01:18:03,156
You helped raise the money with Lane.

913
01:18:03,400 --> 01:18:05,755
You came through for me.

914
01:18:06,040 --> 01:18:08,952
It's set up.
We meet them tomorrow.

915
01:18:09,200 --> 01:18:10,189
No.

916
01:18:11,560 --> 01:18:14,518
Get the fuck away from me.
You're crazy.

917
01:18:14,920 --> 01:18:16,911
I'm not going anywhere.

918
01:18:20,920 --> 01:18:24,515
Where's the money?
I need the quarter mil.

919
01:18:24,960 --> 01:18:27,030
Where is she?
Where is she?!

920
01:18:27,320 --> 01:18:31,359
You can't win here, Ray.
Dealer holds the cards.

921
01:18:32,400 --> 01:18:35,915
Look, hey, we'll trade Lane
for the cash.

922
01:18:36,760 --> 01:18:39,320
She said you had it. See you.

923
01:18:43,480 --> 01:18:45,516
Bury them if you want.

924
01:19:00,480 --> 01:19:01,913
Lane?

925
01:19:04,200 --> 01:19:05,519
Lane!

926
01:19:21,200 --> 01:19:26,115
ARMS DEALER: <i>Ever been to White Sands?</i>
<i>It's not sand. It's gypsum.</i>

927
01:19:46,360 --> 01:19:48,396
Man, not this noise again!

928
01:19:51,880 --> 01:19:54,075
We're going for a little ride.

929
01:21:37,920 --> 01:21:40,309
It's easier if you rip it off.

930
01:21:40,560 --> 01:21:43,916
Oh, shit! You son of a bitch!

931
01:21:44,120 --> 01:21:46,634
You'll see the light soon...

932
01:21:46,880 --> 01:21:51,351
...and remember the only way out
is to help me get Lennox!

933
01:21:53,000 --> 01:21:56,117
Guess what, Greg? Lennox is CIA.

934
01:21:58,760 --> 01:22:00,193
That's bullshit!

935
01:22:07,680 --> 01:22:10,956
Who the fuck told you that? Ray!

936
01:22:11,200 --> 01:22:15,830
So what if he's CIA?
So what if he's in on Artie's deal?

937
01:22:16,080 --> 01:22:20,551
It's not gonna save your ass!
You're losing it, Ray!

938
01:22:20,800 --> 01:22:23,712
Losing it the same way Artie did!

939
01:22:24,000 --> 01:22:26,753
We both know
what happened to him!

940
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:31,710
The farther you go down that river,
the harder it is to return!

941
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:37,309
You listening to me, Ray?

942
01:22:40,160 --> 01:22:44,915
Last night, that call I made?
FBI Internal Affairs in D.C.

943
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:50,029
I said I was Artie's accomplice,
and I'd meet them here.

944
01:22:50,280 --> 01:22:51,918
I don't get it.

945
01:22:54,560 --> 01:22:58,235
Lennox killed the feds
who think I'm the accomplice.

946
01:22:58,520 --> 01:23:02,354
Anybody could be
Artie's accomplice now, right?

947
01:23:02,600 --> 01:23:04,318
Anybody.

948
01:23:05,400 --> 01:23:09,552
- Like you, for instance.
- Oh, man. Look, Ray...

949
01:23:10,000 --> 01:23:13,037
- Don't do this!
- I told them to send one guy.

950
01:23:13,280 --> 01:23:17,751
Just one, or I'd bolt.
My first concern being the operation.

951
01:23:18,000 --> 01:23:20,912
You know this is not gonna work!

952
01:23:22,320 --> 01:23:25,551
You got lots to think about. Choices.

953
01:23:25,840 --> 01:23:30,152
You could try
to explain everything to the FBI.

954
01:23:30,400 --> 01:23:35,030
It's a long shot, but you are
a senior minority agent...

955
01:23:35,280 --> 01:23:38,192
...without even a bug stain
on your record.

956
01:23:38,480 --> 01:23:42,519
Or you could kill him
and take the money and run.

957
01:23:57,400 --> 01:23:58,992
You like choices?

958
01:25:01,200 --> 01:25:03,236
I'm glad you got my clue.

959
01:25:14,760 --> 01:25:17,752
Where's Lane? That was the deal.

960
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:20,912
She's down the road, by the entrance.

961
01:25:22,200 --> 01:25:25,829
- You don't trust me.
- Where's the money?

962
01:25:27,160 --> 01:25:30,675
Oh, it's right in there.

963
01:25:37,680 --> 01:25:42,708
- Why'd you put it in there?
- I wanted a chance to get away.

964
01:25:42,960 --> 01:25:45,315
You're so goddamn cynical.

965
01:25:54,120 --> 01:25:56,315
I thought you quit smoking.

966
01:25:59,280 --> 01:26:01,919
Looks like I have no willpower.

967
01:26:03,000 --> 01:26:06,117
You sure the money's in the case?

968
01:26:06,320 --> 01:26:09,756
I thought we had a mutual trust here.

969
01:26:10,600 --> 01:26:12,318
You're making me sad.

970
01:26:18,120 --> 01:26:21,112
Maybe we can hook up again someday.

971
01:26:21,360 --> 01:26:23,920
No. Too wild for me.

972
01:26:25,880 --> 01:26:29,111
It's a bunch of bureaucratic bullshit.

973
01:26:29,320 --> 01:26:34,314
They have an agenda, so do I.
But you know what? It works.

974
01:26:34,560 --> 01:26:36,915
Yeah, it's the CIA way.

975
01:26:37,120 --> 01:26:41,318
It's beautiful.
It keeps corruption to a minimum.

976
01:26:43,120 --> 01:26:46,351
I'm gonna go while you're in there.

